ciscoScsiFlowMIB.name: ciscoScsiFlowMIB
ciscoScsiFlowMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS mail: cs-san@cisco.com
ciscoScsiFlowMIB.description: A SCSI Flow is described as a SCSI Initiator SCSI Target combination. This MIB is used to configure and monitor SCSI Flows. Glossary of terms used in this MIB: ABTS - Abort Sequence. ACA - Acquire Change Authorization. CFS - Cisco Fabric Service is a general mechanism to distribute data within a Storage Area Network. DPP - Data Path Processor. ILC - Intelligent Line Card. LUN - Logical Unit Number is a 64-bit identifier for a logical unit. pWWN - port World Wide Name. nWWN - node World Wide Name. SCSI Initiator - is a device that contains application clients and SCSI initiator ports that originate device service and task management requests to be processed by a target SCSI device. SCSI flow - connection between SCSI initiator and SCSI target. SCSI Target - is a device that contains logical units and SCSI target ports that receive device service and task management requests for processing. SFC - SCSI Flow Client. SFM - SCSI Flow Manager. TCAM - Ternary Content Addressable Memory. VSAN - Virtual Storage Area Network, similar to a VLAN. WWN - World Wide Name. Mechanism of identifying devices in Fibre Channel Networks. It is 8 bytes long.

CSFlowDeviceType.name: CSFlowDeviceType
CSFlowDeviceType.description: Represents the type of SCSI device. initiator(1) - the device is a SCSI initiator. target(2) - the device is a SCSI target.

CSFlowVerifyReasonCode.name: CSFlowVerifyReasonCode
CSFlowVerifyReasonCode.description: Represents the reason codes associated with SCSI flow verification notifications. success(1) - successful. noLicense(2) - there was no license available. generalError(3) - generic error. notInNameServer(4) - device was not found in Name Server database. notInFlogiServer(5) - device was not found in FLOGI Server database. deviceNotOnIlc(6) - device was not on Intelligent Line card. deviceNotScsi(7) - device was not SCSI device. deviceNotInitiator(8) - device was not initiator. deviceNotTarget(9) - device was not target. deviceNotFibreChannel(10) - device was not a Fibre Channel device. ipcTimeout(11) - internal IPC timeout. cfsError(12) - Cisco Fabric Service has reported error. cfsTimeout(13) - Cisco Fabric Service has timed out. portsUnprovisioned(14) - ports have not been provisioned. initTargetZonedOut(15) - Initiator and target have been zoned out. statusNotChecked(16) - The device status has not been checked. initNotInNameServer(17) - The initiator was not found in Name Server database. tgtNotInNameServer(18) - The target was not found in Name Server database. tgtNotInFlogiServer(19) - The target was not found in FLOGI Server database.

CSFlowCfgReasonCode.name: CSFlowCfgReasonCode
CSFlowCfgReasonCode.description: Represents the reason code associated with SCSI flow feature configuration notifications. success(1) - successful. ipcError(2) - IPC error. ipcTimeout(3) - IPC timeout. sfmGenericError(4) - SCSI Flow Manager error. sfcGenericError(5) - SCSI Flow Client error. cfsError(6) - Cisco Fabric Service error. cfsTimeout(7) - Cisco Fabric Service timeout. deviceNotOnIlc(8) - device was not on Intelligent Line Card. lcIpcError(9) - Line card IPC error. tcamError(10) - Hardware programming (TCAM) error. ilcAsicDrvError(11) - Intelligent Line Card ASIC driver error. dppError(12) - Data Path Processor error. statusNotChecked(13) - The configuration status has not been checked. sfcDBError(14) - SCSI Flow Client process on ILC gives Database error. sfcNoSuchFlow(15) - No such flow exists on SFC process on ILC. sfcFlowExists(16) - The flow already exists on the SFC process on ILC. dppNoBuffers(17) - No free buffers are available on the DPP. dppNoMemory(18) - No more memory is available on the DPP. dppFlowExists(19) - Flow already exists on the DPP.

CSFlowFeatureCfgReasonCode.name: CSFlowFeatureCfgReasonCode
CSFlowFeatureCfgReasonCode.description: Represents the reason code to be used with SCSI flow feature configuration notifications. success(1) - successful. featureCfgFailure(2) - failure in configuring the feature. flowVerifFailure(3) - flow verification failure.

ciscoScsiFlowNextIndexAvail.name: ciscoScsiFlowNextIndexAvail
ciscoScsiFlowNextIndexAvail.description: This object contains the next available value for the object ciscoScsiFlowId. If all values are exhausted, then this object will contain a 0 value. A management application should read this object, get the (non-zero) value and use same for creating an entry in the ciscoScsiFlowTable. If two network management applications read this object at the same time and try to create an entry in the ciscoScsiFlowTable, only one of them will succeed. The network management application which failed, will need to re-read this object and try the SET again.

ciscoScsiFlowTable.name: ciscoScsiFlowTable
ciscoScsiFlowTable.description: This table allows configuration of SCSI flows. The Initiator should be connected to a port on an Intelligent Line Card on the local switch. The Target device can be present anywhere in the network. The management application should create entries in this table for all SCSI flows it is interested in. This table contains all the SCSI flows configured on the local device. A SCSI flow is identified uniquely by a SCSI flow ID.

ciscoScsiFlowEntry.name: ciscoScsiFlowEntry
ciscoScsiFlowEntry.description: An entry, which is uniquely identified by the SCSI flow ID, contains the various attributes of a SCSI flow.

ciscoScsiFlowId.name: ciscoScsiFlowId
ciscoScsiFlowId.description: This object represents the flow identifier.

ciscoScsiFlowIntrWwn.name: ciscoScsiFlowIntrWwn
ciscoScsiFlowIntrWwn.description: This object represents the pWWN of the Initiator in the flow. This object must be set to a valid value before or concurrently setting the corresponding instance of ciscoScsiFlowRowStatus object to 'active'.

ciscoScsiFlowTargetWwn.name: ciscoScsiFlowTargetWwn
ciscoScsiFlowTargetWwn.description: This object represents the pWWN of the Target in the flow. This object must be set to a valid value before or concurrently setting the corresponding instance of ciscoScsiFlowRowStatus object to 'active'.

ciscoScsiFlowIntrVsan.name: ciscoScsiFlowIntrVsan
ciscoScsiFlowIntrVsan.description: The VSAN ID of the initiator on which the flow is configured.

ciscoScsiFlowTargetVsan.name: ciscoScsiFlowTargetVsan
ciscoScsiFlowTargetVsan.description: The VSAN ID of the target on which the flow is configured.

ciscoScsiFlowAllLuns.name: ciscoScsiFlowAllLuns
ciscoScsiFlowAllLuns.description: If this object is set to 'true', it specifies that all the LUNs on the target are to be included in the flow.

ciscoScsiFlowWriteAcc.name: ciscoScsiFlowWriteAcc
ciscoScsiFlowWriteAcc.description: This object specifies if write-acceleration feature is enabled for this flow. If set to 'true' it is enabled. If set to 'false', it is disabled.

ciscoScsiFlowBufCount.name: ciscoScsiFlowBufCount
ciscoScsiFlowBufCount.description: The value of this object is relevant only if the corresponding instance of ciscoScsiFlowWriteAcc has been set to 'true'. It specifies the number of buffers to be used for write-acceleration.

ciscoScsiFlowStatsEnabled.name: ciscoScsiFlowStatsEnabled
ciscoScsiFlowStatsEnabled.description: This object specifies if the statistics gathering needs to be enabled for this flow. If it is set to 'true', then it is enabled. If it is set to 'false', then it is disabled.

ciscoScsiFlowClearStats.name: ciscoScsiFlowClearStats
ciscoScsiFlowClearStats.description: This object assists in clearing the statistics for this flow. If this object is set to 'clear(1)', it results in all statistics for this flow being cleared. No action is taken if it is set to 'noop(2)'. The value of this object when read is always 'noop(2)'.

ciscoScsiFlowIntrVrfStatus.name: ciscoScsiFlowIntrVrfStatus
ciscoScsiFlowIntrVrfStatus.description: The verification status of the initiator device corresponding to the SCSI Flow.

ciscoScsiFlowTgtVrfStatus.name: ciscoScsiFlowTgtVrfStatus
ciscoScsiFlowTgtVrfStatus.description: The verification status of the target device corresponding to the SCSI Flow.

ciscoScsiFlowIntrLCStatus.name: ciscoScsiFlowIntrLCStatus
ciscoScsiFlowIntrLCStatus.description: The status of the linecard where the SCSI Flow initiator device is located.

ciscoScsiFlowTgtLCStatus.name: ciscoScsiFlowTgtLCStatus
ciscoScsiFlowTgtLCStatus.description: The status of the linecard where the SCSI Flow target device is located.

ciscoScsiFlowRowStatus.name: ciscoScsiFlowRowStatus
ciscoScsiFlowRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row. When creating an entry in this table, the management application MUST set values for the corresponding instances of ciscoScsiFlowIntrWwn and ciscoScsiFlowTargetWwn before or concurrently with setting this object to 'active'.

ciscoScsiFlowNum.name: ciscoScsiFlowNum
ciscoScsiFlowNum.description: This object indicates the flow ID corresponding to which notifications need to be sent.

ciscoScsiFlowDeviceType.name: ciscoScsiFlowDeviceType
ciscoScsiFlowDeviceType.description: This object indicates whether the notification pertains to an initiator or target.

ciscoScsiFlowVerifyReasonCode.name: ciscoScsiFlowVerifyReasonCode
ciscoScsiFlowVerifyReasonCode.description: This object indicates the verification reason code to be included in notifications.

ciscoScsiFlowCfgReasonCode.name: ciscoScsiFlowCfgReasonCode
ciscoScsiFlowCfgReasonCode.description: This object indicates the feature configuration reason code to be included in notifications.

ciscoScsiFlowStatsTable.name: ciscoScsiFlowStatsTable
ciscoScsiFlowStatsTable.description: A table containing statistics related to SCSI flows on active LUNs. Counters in this table pertaining to a flow on a LUN will be populated if the corresponding statistics gathering object for that flow (ciscoScsiFlowStatsEnabled) is enabled and I/Os have been done to that LUN. The management application can cause entries to be created in this table by setting the appropriate instance of ciscoScsiFlowStatsEnabled object.

ciscoScsiFlowStatsEntry.name: ciscoScsiFlowStatsEntry
ciscoScsiFlowStatsEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in this table. An entry contains the statistics related to a LUN on a flow.

ciscoScsiFlowLunId.name: ciscoScsiFlowLunId
ciscoScsiFlowLunId.description: The LUN ID on this flow on which the statistics are gathered.

ciscoScsiFlowRdIos.name: ciscoScsiFlowRdIos
ciscoScsiFlowRdIos.description: The total number of SCSI read operations on this LUN on this flow.

ciscoScsiFlowRdFailedIos.name: ciscoScsiFlowRdFailedIos
ciscoScsiFlowRdFailedIos.description: The total number of SCSI read operations that have failed on this LUN on this flow.

ciscoScsiFlowRdTimeouts.name: ciscoScsiFlowRdTimeouts
ciscoScsiFlowRdTimeouts.description: The total number of SCSI read operations that have timed out on this LUN on this flow.

ciscoScsiFlowRdBlocks.name: ciscoScsiFlowRdBlocks
ciscoScsiFlowRdBlocks.description: The total number of blocks that have been read on this LUN on this flow.

ciscoScsiFlowRdMaxBlocks.name: ciscoScsiFlowRdMaxBlocks
ciscoScsiFlowRdMaxBlocks.description: The maximum number of blocks read across all read operations on this LUN on this flow.

ciscoScsiFlowRdMinTime.name: ciscoScsiFlowRdMinTime
ciscoScsiFlowRdMinTime.description: The minimum response time over all read operations on this LUN on this flow.

ciscoScsiFlowRdMaxTime.name: ciscoScsiFlowRdMaxTime
ciscoScsiFlowRdMaxTime.description: The maximum response time over all read operations on this LUN on this flow.

ciscoScsiFlowRdsActive.name: ciscoScsiFlowRdsActive
ciscoScsiFlowRdsActive.description: The number of read operations that are currently active on this LUN on this flow.

ciscoScsiFlowWrIos.name: ciscoScsiFlowWrIos
ciscoScsiFlowWrIos.description: The total number of SCSI write operations on this LUN on this flow.

ciscoScsiFlowWrFailedIos.name: ciscoScsiFlowWrFailedIos
ciscoScsiFlowWrFailedIos.description: The total number of SCSI write operations that have failed on this LUN on this flow.

ciscoScsiFlowWrTimeouts.name: ciscoScsiFlowWrTimeouts
ciscoScsiFlowWrTimeouts.description: The total number of SCSI write operations that have timed out on this LUN on this flow.

ciscoScsiFlowWrBlocks.name: ciscoScsiFlowWrBlocks
ciscoScsiFlowWrBlocks.description: The total number of blocks that have been written on this LUN on this flow.

ciscoScsiFlowWrMaxBlocks.name: ciscoScsiFlowWrMaxBlocks
ciscoScsiFlowWrMaxBlocks.description: The maximum number of blocks written across all write operations on this LUN on this flow.

ciscoScsiFlowWrMinTime.name: ciscoScsiFlowWrMinTime
ciscoScsiFlowWrMinTime.description: The minimum response time over all write operations on this LUN on this flow.

ciscoScsiFlowWrMaxTime.name: ciscoScsiFlowWrMaxTime
ciscoScsiFlowWrMaxTime.description: The maximum response time over all write operations on this LUN on this flow.

ciscoScsiFlowWrsActive.name: ciscoScsiFlowWrsActive
ciscoScsiFlowWrsActive.description: The number of write operations that are currently active on this LUN on this flow.

ciscoScsiFlowTestUnitRdys.name: ciscoScsiFlowTestUnitRdys
ciscoScsiFlowTestUnitRdys.description: The number of test unit ready SCSI commands sent on this LUN on this flow.

ciscoScsiFlowRepLuns.name: ciscoScsiFlowRepLuns
ciscoScsiFlowRepLuns.description: The number of Report LUN SCSI commands sent on this LUN on this flow.

ciscoScsiFlowInquirys.name: ciscoScsiFlowInquirys
ciscoScsiFlowInquirys.description: The number of SCSI Inquiry commands sent on this LUN on this flow.

ciscoScsiFlowRdCapacitys.name: ciscoScsiFlowRdCapacitys
ciscoScsiFlowRdCapacitys.description: The number of Read Capacity SCSI commands sent on this LUN on this flow.

ciscoScsiFlowModeSenses.name: ciscoScsiFlowModeSenses
ciscoScsiFlowModeSenses.description: The number of Mode Sense SCSI commands sent on this LUN on this flow.

ciscoScsiFlowReqSenses.name: ciscoScsiFlowReqSenses
ciscoScsiFlowReqSenses.description: The number of Request Sense SCSI commands sent on LUN on this this flow.

ciscoScsiFlowRxFc2Frames.name: ciscoScsiFlowRxFc2Frames
ciscoScsiFlowRxFc2Frames.description: The total number of link-level FC frames received on this LUN on this flow.

ciscoScsiFlowTxFc2Frames.name: ciscoScsiFlowTxFc2Frames
ciscoScsiFlowTxFc2Frames.description: The total number of link-level frames transmitted on this LUN on this flow.

ciscoScsiFlowRxFc2Octets.name: ciscoScsiFlowRxFc2Octets
ciscoScsiFlowRxFc2Octets.description: The total number of octets received in link-level frames on this LUN on this flow.

ciscoScsiFlowTxFc2Octets.name: ciscoScsiFlowTxFc2Octets
ciscoScsiFlowTxFc2Octets.description: The total number of octets transmitted in link-level frames on this LUN on this flow.

ciscoScsiFlowBusyStatuses.name: ciscoScsiFlowBusyStatuses
ciscoScsiFlowBusyStatuses.description: The number of busy SCSI statuses received on this LUN on this flow.

ciscoScsiFlowStatusResvConfs.name: ciscoScsiFlowStatusResvConfs
ciscoScsiFlowStatusResvConfs.description: The number of reservation conflicts SCSI status received on this LUN on this flow.

ciscoScsiFlowTskSetFulStatuses.name: ciscoScsiFlowTskSetFulStatuses
ciscoScsiFlowTskSetFulStatuses.description: The number of task set full SCSI statuses received on this LUN on this flow.

ciscoScsiFlowAcaActiveStatuses.name: ciscoScsiFlowAcaActiveStatuses
ciscoScsiFlowAcaActiveStatuses.description: The number of ACA active statuses received on this LUN on this flow.

ciscoScsiFlowSenseKeyNotRdyErrs.name: ciscoScsiFlowSenseKeyNotRdyErrs
ciscoScsiFlowSenseKeyNotRdyErrs.description: The number of NOT READY SCSI SENSE key errors received on this LUN on this flow. This indicates that the logical unit being addressed cannot be accessed.

ciscoScsiFlowSenseKeyMedErrs.name: ciscoScsiFlowSenseKeyMedErrs
ciscoScsiFlowSenseKeyMedErrs.description: The number of MEDIUM ERROR SCSI SENSE key errors received on this LUN on this flow. This indicates that the command terminated with a non-recovered error condition possibly caused by a flaw in the medium.

ciscoScsiFlowSenseKeyHwErrs.name: ciscoScsiFlowSenseKeyHwErrs
ciscoScsiFlowSenseKeyHwErrs.description: The number of HARDWARE ERROR SCSI SENSE key errors received on this LUN on this flow. This indicates that the target detected a non-recoverable hardware failure.

ciscoScsiFlowSenseKeyIllReqErrs.name: ciscoScsiFlowSenseKeyIllReqErrs
ciscoScsiFlowSenseKeyIllReqErrs.description: The number of ILLEGAL REQUEST SCSI SENSE key errors received on this LUN on this flow.

ciscoScsiFlowSenseKeyUnitAttErrs.name: ciscoScsiFlowSenseKeyUnitAttErrs
ciscoScsiFlowSenseKeyUnitAttErrs.description: The number of UNIT ATTENTION SCSI SENSE key errors received on this LUN on this flow.

ciscoScsiFlowSenseKeyDatProtErrs.name: ciscoScsiFlowSenseKeyDatProtErrs
ciscoScsiFlowSenseKeyDatProtErrs.description: The number of DATA PROTECT SCSI SENSE key errors received on this LUN on this flow.

ciscoScsiFlowSenseKeyBlankErrs.name: ciscoScsiFlowSenseKeyBlankErrs
ciscoScsiFlowSenseKeyBlankErrs.description: The number of BLANK CHECK SCSI SENSE key errors received on this LUN on this flow.

ciscoScsiFlowSenseKeyCpAbrtErrs.name: ciscoScsiFlowSenseKeyCpAbrtErrs
ciscoScsiFlowSenseKeyCpAbrtErrs.description: The number of COPY ABORTED SCSI SENSE key errors received on this LUN on this flow.

ciscoScsiFlowSenseKeyAbrtCmdErrs.name: ciscoScsiFlowSenseKeyAbrtCmdErrs
ciscoScsiFlowSenseKeyAbrtCmdErrs.description: The number of ABORTED COMMAND SCSI SENSE key errors received on this LUN on this flow.

ciscoScsiFlowSenseKeyVolFlowErrs.name: ciscoScsiFlowSenseKeyVolFlowErrs
ciscoScsiFlowSenseKeyVolFlowErrs.description: The number of VOLUME OVERFLOW SCSI SENSE key errors received on this LUN on this flow.

ciscoScsiFlowSenseKeyMiscmpErrs.name: ciscoScsiFlowSenseKeyMiscmpErrs
ciscoScsiFlowSenseKeyMiscmpErrs.description: The number of MISCOMPARE SCSI SENSE key errors received on this LUN on this flow.

ciscoScsiFlowAbts.name: ciscoScsiFlowAbts
ciscoScsiFlowAbts.description: The number of ABTSs encountered on this LUN on this flow.

ciscoScsiFlowWrAccStatusTable.name: ciscoScsiFlowWrAccStatusTable
ciscoScsiFlowWrAccStatusTable.description: A table containing status for flows with write-acceleration configured.

ciscoScsiFlowWrAccStatusEntry.name: ciscoScsiFlowWrAccStatusEntry
ciscoScsiFlowWrAccStatusEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in this table. An entry contains the status for write-acceleration feature of the flow.

ciscoScsiFlowWrAccCfgStatus.name: ciscoScsiFlowWrAccCfgStatus
ciscoScsiFlowWrAccCfgStatus.description: The configuration status for write-acceleration feature for this flow.

ciscoScsiFlowWrAccIntrCfgStatus.name: ciscoScsiFlowWrAccIntrCfgStatus
ciscoScsiFlowWrAccIntrCfgStatus.description: The initiator configuration status for write-acceleration feature for this flow.

ciscoScsiFlowWrAccTgtCfgStatus.name: ciscoScsiFlowWrAccTgtCfgStatus
ciscoScsiFlowWrAccTgtCfgStatus.description: The target configuration status for write-acceleration feature for this flow.

ciscoScsiFlowStatsStatusTable.name: ciscoScsiFlowStatsStatusTable
ciscoScsiFlowStatsStatusTable.description: A table containing status for flows with statistics configured.

ciscoScsiFlowStatsStatusEntry.name: ciscoScsiFlowStatsStatusEntry
ciscoScsiFlowStatsStatusEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in this table. An entry contains the status for statistics feature of the flow.

ciscoScsiFlowStatsCfgStatus.name: ciscoScsiFlowStatsCfgStatus
ciscoScsiFlowStatsCfgStatus.description: The configuration status for statistics feature for this flow.

ciscoScsiFlowStatsIntrCfgStatus.name: ciscoScsiFlowStatsIntrCfgStatus
ciscoScsiFlowStatsIntrCfgStatus.description: The initiator configuration status for statistics feature for this flow.

ciscoScsiFlowStatsTgtCfgStatus.name: ciscoScsiFlowStatsTgtCfgStatus
ciscoScsiFlowStatsTgtCfgStatus.description: The target configuration status for statistics feature for this flow.

ciscoScsiFlowVerifyNotify.name: ciscoScsiFlowVerifyNotify
ciscoScsiFlowVerifyNotify.description: This notification is generated whenever a change occurs in the fabric causing a flow to be valid or invalid. The ciscoScsiFlowNum object specifies the flow and the ciscoScsiFlowVerifyReasonCode object specifies the actual reason.

ciscoScsiFlowWrAccNotify.name: ciscoScsiFlowWrAccNotify
ciscoScsiFlowWrAccNotify.description: This notification is generated whenever write acceleration is configured on a flow to indicate the outcome.

ciscoScsiFlowStatsNotify.name: ciscoScsiFlowStatsNotify
ciscoScsiFlowStatsNotify.description: This notification is generated whenever statistics gathering is configured on a flow to indicate the outcome.

ciscoScsiFlowMIBCompliance.name: ciscoScsiFlowMIBCompliance
ciscoScsiFlowMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities that implement the CISCO-SCSI-FLOW-MIB.

ciscoScsiFlowGroup.name: ciscoScsiFlowGroup
ciscoScsiFlowGroup.description: A set of objects for configuring SCSI flows.

ciscoScsiFlowStatsGroup.name: ciscoScsiFlowStatsGroup
ciscoScsiFlowStatsGroup.description: A collection of objects for displaying SCSI flow statistics.

ciscoScsiFlowInfoGroup.name: ciscoScsiFlowInfoGroup
ciscoScsiFlowInfoGroup.description: A collection of notification information objects for notification generation.

ciscoScsiFlowNotifyGroup.name: ciscoScsiFlowNotifyGroup
ciscoScsiFlowNotifyGroup.description: A collection of notifications for monitoring SCSI flows.

ciscoScsiFlowFeatureStatusGroup.name: ciscoScsiFlowFeatureStatusGroup
ciscoScsiFlowFeatureStatusGroup.description: A collection of objects for monitoring feature status on SCSI flows.
